00:28:36,012 --> 00:28:37,262
Step back, sir.

507
00:28:41,595 --> 00:28:42,645
She's down.

508
00:28:48,939 --> 00:28:50,186
We found Sally Alvarez.

509
00:28:50,627 --> 00:28:53,147
She's been dead for about six hours.
Blunt force trauma to the head.

510
00:28:53,315 --> 00:28:56,317
She's dead? My god.
That's amazing.

511
00:28:56,612 --> 00:28:58,402
- Why?
- Kristina Frye

512
00:28:58,570 --> 00:29:00,404
said Sally passed over.
She predicted it.

513
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:02,572
- She did?
- Can I have that?

514
00:29:03,599 --> 00:29:05,755
Please do not believe
this mystic mumbo jumbo.

515
00:29:05,880 --> 00:29:08,204
Gullible Grace buried the lead.
I was right.

516
00:29:08,697 --> 00:29:10,706
- There were two Carmen.
- There were?

517
00:29:10,874 --> 00:29:13,219
That's right,
and we have the real one right here.

518
00:29:13,344 --> 00:29:14,494
Carmen Reyes.

519
00:29:17,297 --> 00:29:19,215
She claims to be
Hector Brava's daughter.

520
00:29:23,046 --> 00:29:25,805
A year ago,
my mother's diagnosed with cancer.

521
00:29:27,424 --> 00:29:29,082
It got bad very fast.

522
00:29:29,393 --> 00:29:31,435
She was gone in less than a month.

523
00:29:32,219 --> 00:29:35,064
Before she died, she told me
Hector Brava was my father.

524
00:29:35,948 --> 00:29:38,313
And after the funeral,
I wrote to him.

525
00:29:39,532 --> 00:29:40,653
I never heard back.

526
00:29:41,479 --> 00:29:42,479
I thought

527
00:29:42,864 --> 00:29:44,558
maybe he'd forgotten her.

528
00:29:45,484 --> 00:29:47,720
I wrote there was nothing
I wanted from him,

529
00:29:48,001 --> 00:29:49,787
only to meet the man
who was my father.

530
00:29:49,955 --> 00:29:51,247
He still didn't answer?

531
00:29:53,612 --> 00:29:56,127
I saw somewhere
that he was delivering a speech here.

532
00:29:58,321 --> 00:29:59,964
I thought i'd go confront him.

533
00:30:00,643 --> 00:30:01,674
You were angry.

534
00:30:02,258 --> 00:30:04,301
- I wanted to talk to him.
- Did you?

535
00:30:06,430 --> 00:30:07,430
When?

536
00:30:07,898 --> 00:30:08,973
The morning he died?

537
00:30:10,047 --> 00:30:11,359
The night before.

538
00:30:12,592 --> 00:30:13,936
I went to his suite.

539
00:30:14,460 --> 00:30:15,271
And?

540
00:30:17,049 --> 00:30:18,107
He let me in.

541
00:30:19,883 --> 00:30:21,117
He was friendly,

542
00:30:22,242 --> 00:30:24,442
until I told him I s his daughter.

543
00:30:25,523 --> 00:30:26,523
He got

544
00:30:26,987 --> 00:30:29,258
very upset and angry.

545
00:30:31,242 --> 00:30:33,289
He said,
I could not be his daughter.

546
00:30:33,582 --> 00:30:35,499
He said,
he already met his daughter,

547
00:30:35,709 --> 00:30:37,710
and what kind of scam
was I trying to play?

548
00:30:38,962 --> 00:30:41,255
He turned so pale and shook

549
00:30:41,482 --> 00:30:42,482
all over.

550
00:30:43,175 --> 00:30:45,301
He threw me out of the room
and locked the door,

551
00:30:47,669 --> 00:30:48,669
so I left.

552
00:30:52,599 --> 00:30:54,101
That was last time you saw him?

553
00:30:56,624 --> 00:30:58,650
On the news, it said what happened.

554
00:31:01,051 --> 00:31:02,485
I didn't know what to do.

555
00:31:03,453 --> 00:31:05,946
And what about the text message?
Did you send that?

556
00:31:07,253 --> 00:31:08,803
I don't have a phone.

557
00:31:09,482 --> 00:31:11,327
So is she telling the truth?

558
00:31:11,840 --> 00:31:12,990
I'm not sure.

559
00:31:13,426 --> 00:31:14,997
Brava's spirit is deeply conflicted.

560
00:31:15,165 --> 00:31:16,749
I can't get a clear reading.

561
00:31:16,917 --> 00:31:18,667
What are you using, dial-up?

562
00:31:20,504 --> 00:31:21,504
My question,

563
00:31:21,672 --> 00:31:23,923
is if she's telling the truth,
why was Sally Alvarez

564
00:31:24,091 --> 00:31:25,859
pretending to be Carmen Reyes?

565
00:31:26,234 --> 00:31:28,511
I talked to Bigelow.
He kept a record of all work

566
00:31:28,679 --> 00:31:31,514
correspondences but didn't have anything
to do with Brava's personal letters.

567
00:31:31,682 --> 00:31:33,516
No way to know
if she tell the truth.

568
00:31:33,684 --> 00:31:35,476
If Brava's her father,
she's got motive.

569
00:31:35,644 --> 00:31:36,886
She's not the only one.

570
00:31:40,884 --> 00:31:42,737
I could never have children.

571
00:31:45,903 --> 00:31:46,904
Is it true?

572
00:31:47,552 --> 00:31:48,989
Is she really she's daughter?

573
00:31:49,663 --> 00:31:50,908
We don't know, Ma'am.

574
00:31:51,076 --> 00:31:52,868
She's agreed to take
a paternity test.

575
00:31:53,036 --> 00:31:54,620
She might be telling the truth.

576
00:31:55,143 --> 00:31:57,122
You think she might be the one
that killed hector.

577
00:31:57,395 --> 00:31:59,792
Maybe...
And then maybe it was you.

578
00:32:00,140 --> 00:32:01,829
I have to say, Ma'am,

579
00:32:02,254 --> 00:32:05,047
it's pretty hard to believe
that you didn't know about his behavior.

580
00:32:05,950 --> 00:32:06,757
I knew.

581
00:32:07,745 --> 00:32:09,927
Hector was a passionate
and heroic man who devoted

582
00:32:10,095 --> 00:32:11,554
himself to helping others.

583
00:32:11,722 --> 00:32:14,223
His flaws
were correspondingly oversized.

584
00:32:14,391 --> 00:32:16,413
And his behavior was okay with you?

585
00:32:17,082 --> 00:32:18,349
I accepted it.

586
00:32:19,193 --> 00:32:21,023
The good in him outweighed the bad.

587
00:32:23,108 --> 00:32:25,799
If he'd told me, maybe
I could've done something to prevent it.

588
00:32:27,984 --> 00:32:29,780
- Maybe I could've saved him.
- What for?

589
00:32:30,328 --> 00:32:33,260
How could you not want to get away
from his serial philandering,

590
00:32:33,630 --> 00:32:35,366
from the prison
of your loveless marriage?

591
00:32:35,491 --> 00:32:36,620
That's not true!

592
00:32:36,788 --> 00:32:37,871
I loved my husband,

593
00:32:38,219 --> 00:32:39,331
and he loved me!

594
00:32:39,499 --> 00:32:41,250
Maybe we can get in contact
with him now.

595
00:32:42,068 --> 00:32:43,616
You could do that, couldn't you?

596
00:32:43,741 --> 00:32:45,763
It would certainly clear up
a few things.

597
00:32:47,862 --> 00:32:49,008
Would you do that?

598
00:32:49,647 --> 00:32:51,093
Would you talk to my husband?

599
00:32:51,465 --> 00:32:52,469
Yes, ilsa.

600
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:55,097
- What are you doing?
- What does it look like I'm doing?

601
00:32:57,062 --> 00:32:59,490
Okay, so Van Pelt
is bringing Carmen.

602
00:32:59,615 --> 00:33:01,719
Rigsby's gonna bring
Richard Bigelow.

603
00:33:01,844 --> 00:33:03,652
Cho is gonna pick up Tariq Sharif

604
00:33:03,921 --> 00:33:05,816
and Stacey.
So we're all set.

605
00:33:06,127 --> 00:33:08,428
- What's all set for what?
- We're all set for,

606
00:33:08,553 --> 00:33:11,313
Kristina Frye
to contact Hector Brava's spirit.

607
00:33:11,438 --> 00:33:13,449
I need everybody connected
with his passing.

608
00:33:14,814 --> 00:33:16,160
Well, I guess...

609
00:33:16,855 --> 00:33:19,208
Just make sure Brava's spirit
has a thirst for revenge.

610
00:33:19,333 --> 00:33:21,531
He wants to put some kind
of a curse on the killer, okay?

611
00:33:21,656 --> 00:33:23,793
That kind of thing.
And I'll take it from there.

612
00:33:23,918 --> 00:33:25,210
I can't do that.

613
00:33:25,754 --> 00:33:28,464
Yes, you can. It is a necessary lie.

614
00:33:28,923 --> 00:33:31,949
I can only contact hector Brava's spirit
and speak as he wants me to.

615
00:33:32,074 --> 00:33:34,225
To do otherwise
would be to abuse my gift.

616
00:33:40,595 --> 00:33:43,105
- Everything okay?
- Yep. Everything's good. It's perfect.

617
00:33:46,967 --> 00:33:48,223
Are we starting now?

618
00:33:48,348 --> 00:33:50,486
- Almost.
- I'll just get the door.

619
00:33:51,847 --> 00:33:52,847
Welcome.

620
00:33:53,923 --> 00:33:54,967
Come on in.

621
00:33:57,411 --> 00:33:58,452
Thanks for coming.

622
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:02,080
It was your husband's request.

623
00:34:04,145 --> 00:34:05,447
Your husband's daughter.

624
00:34:18,048 --> 00:34:19,409
Thank you all for coming.

625
00:34:20,267 --> 00:34:21,731
Patrick will be assisting me.

626
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:25,771
So in order for this to work,
I need everybody to be calm and focused.

627
00:34:26,945 --> 00:34:29,420
I want you to look at the candle
in the center of the table.

628
00:34:30,101 --> 00:34:31,402
Focus on the flame

629
00:34:31,742 --> 00:34:33,255
and concentrate on Hector.

630
00:34:52,665 --> 00:34:53,674
He's here.

631
00:34:56,808 --> 00:34:57,876
I can feel him.

632
00:35:03,530 --> 00:35:05,477
Who do you wish to speak to?

633
00:35:10,912 --> 00:35:12,025
The killer's here.

634
00:35:16,777 --> 00:35:17,844
Know this...

635
00:35:18,983 --> 00:35:20,637
Hector Brava says...

636
00:35:21,353 --> 00:35:22,655
vengeance will come.

637
00:35:24,590 --> 00:35:26,104
Your blood will spill...

638
00:35:26,666 --> 00:35:28,039
Before the rising sun.

639
00:35:31,518 --> 00:35:32,703
I sense him.

640
00:35:36,961 --> 00:35:38,755
I can almost see an image.

641
00:35:39,060 --> 00:35:40,104
It's hazy.

642
00:35:46,562 --> 00:35:47,958
It's as if it could just...

643
00:35:48,083 --> 00:35:50,198
Hector, wait.
Stop. Don't go.

644
00:35:51,418 --> 00:35:53,066
Show us who the killer is.

645
00:35:53,925 --> 00:35:55,051
There it is.

646
00:35:56,236 --> 00:35:57,236
A door.

647
00:35:58,666 --> 00:36:00,050
"Employees only."

648
00:36:02,173 --> 00:36:03,604
And an empty hallway.

649
00:36:05,610 --> 00:36:06,677
Footsteps...

650
00:36:07,721 --> 00:36:08,730
Close...

651
00:36:10,149 --> 00:36:11,158
Close...

652
00:36:14,589 --> 00:36:15,380
I see you.

653
00:36:18,285 --> 00:36:20,719
I'm sorry.
You scared me to death with that.

654
00:36:21,769 --> 00:36:23,806
It's okay. You can relax, Bigelow.
It's over.

655
00:36:25,223 --> 00:36:26,600
I know it was you that did it.

656
00:36:26,873 --> 00:36:28,685
Because I got frantic
and I'm fell out?

657
00:36:28,853 --> 00:36:31,647
Because you managed Brava's
correspondence, you were the first one

658
00:36:31,815 --> 00:36:33,273
to read Carmen's letters, yes?

659
00:36:33,441 --> 00:36:35,442
You set Brava up
on a date with sally

660
00:36:35,610 --> 00:36:38,028
and had her pretend to be Carmen,
and then you told Brava

661
00:36:38,153 --> 00:36:39,822
that he had sex with his daughter.

662
00:36:40,145 --> 00:36:40,948
Lord.

663
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:43,909
And then the real deal showed up,

664
00:36:45,203 --> 00:36:46,578
you faked Carmen's message,

665
00:36:47,325 --> 00:36:50,332
and when Brava walked through
that service door, you killed him.

666
00:36:50,599 --> 00:36:52,334
And you killed poor Sally Alvarez

667
00:36:52,502 --> 00:36:53,884
to cover your tracks.

668
00:36:55,033 --> 00:36:57,130
And now you'll pay
for the crime you committed.

669
00:36:58,591 --> 00:37:00,926
Your blood will spill
before the sun rises.

670
00:37:01,094 --> 00:37:02,636
That part I'm not so sure about.

671
00:37:11,145 --> 00:37:12,412
It came in the mail.

672
00:37:13,409 --> 00:37:15,004
Just out of the blue.
Just a...

673
00:37:16,343 --> 00:37:19,392
Letter describing
an affair Brava had 20 years ago,

674
00:37:20,401 --> 00:37:21,903
naming the woman and the place.

675
00:37:22,028 --> 00:37:24,157
And that came from Carmen Reyes.
The real Carmen.

676
00:37:26,202 --> 00:37:28,111
That gave you all
the facts you needed...

677
00:37:28,236 --> 00:37:31,313
Things about the affair that only Brava
and Carmen's mother would know.

678
00:37:31,970 --> 00:37:33,190
- Right?
- Yeah.

679
00:37:42,259 --> 00:37:43,427
So why'd you do it?

680
00:37:45,203 --> 00:37:47,264
Why put a man through that kind
of suffering?

681
00:37:49,338 --> 00:37:52,165
Was it the money? Or did you just like
having Brava in your power?

682
00:37:54,841 --> 00:37:57,949
Do you know I've been running numbers
on trafficking for Brava

683
00:37:58,207 --> 00:38:01,105
and setting him up on his dates for,
like, five years?

684
00:38:02,196 --> 00:38:03,914
And do you think that he ever,

685
00:38:05,310 --> 00:38:06,617
ever thanked me?

686
00:38:07,327 --> 00:38:08,594
Said, "I'm sorry"?

687
00:38:09,405 --> 00:38:12,009
Said, "I'm gonna make this up
to you one day, Russell"?

688
00:38:14,273 --> 00:38:15,305
I knew Sally

689
00:38:15,868 --> 00:38:17,182
from a whorehouse

690
00:38:17,558 --> 00:38:19,004
up in Northern California.

691
00:38:19,515 --> 00:38:21,614
I told her if
she pretended to be Carmen,

692
00:38:21,896 --> 00:38:24,217
we could blackmail Brava
and split the money.

693
00:38:24,488 --> 00:38:26,486
The letter just gave us
everything we needed

694
00:38:26,611 --> 00:38:28,931
to make Brava think that
she was the real deal.

695
00:38:29,913 --> 00:38:32,953
And he was not one for asking
a whole lot of questions, so...

696
00:38:36,589 --> 00:38:38,960
- Then the real Carmen showed up.
- Yeah.

697
00:38:39,818 --> 00:38:41,810
He called me
as soon as she left his room,

698
00:38:42,561 --> 00:38:43,570
freaked.

699
00:38:44,743 --> 00:38:45,812
So I played dumb.

700
00:38:46,029 --> 00:38:46,823
But then

701
00:38:46,991 --> 00:38:48,709
the next morning, he called me

702
00:38:49,061 --> 00:38:50,577
and he said, "we need to talk."

703
00:38:51,092 --> 00:38:53,919
- It was pretty clear he figured it out.
- And so you went to the hotel

704
00:38:54,044 --> 00:38:56,007
and texted Brava
from the service hallway.

705
00:39:19,599 --> 00:39:21,441
I just wanted to keep him quiet.

706
00:39:21,609 --> 00:39:22,813
And Sally Alvarez?

707
00:39:23,130 --> 00:39:24,903
You had to keep her quiet,
too, right?

708
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:30,732
I was a really good researcher.

709
00:39:31,744 --> 00:39:32,744
I bet.

710
00:39:43,766 --> 00:39:45,817
Agent Van Pelt,
you wanted to see me?

711
00:39:46,617 --> 00:39:49,764
Yeah. I just wanted to go over
a few things in your statement.

712
00:39:49,889 --> 00:39:51,579
Let's go in the kitchen.

713
00:40:03,083 --> 00:40:04,443
Nice working with you.

714
00:40:07,682 --> 00:40:10,298
You were very good back there.
You almost had me with the whole

715
00:40:10,423 --> 00:40:13,493
"I can't misuse my gift for fear
of what might happen" bit.

716
00:40:13,922 --> 00:40:15,342
I did what I said I would.

717
00:40:15,871 --> 00:40:19,191
I spoke the words the spirits
told me to speak, nothing more.

718
00:40:19,695 --> 00:40:20,695
Really?

719
00:40:22,545 --> 00:40:24,064
Don't you know me by now?

720
00:40:24,534 --> 00:40:26,840
Don't you know I wouldn't lie
about a thing like that?

721
00:40:27,502 --> 00:40:28,300
Ms. Frye,

722
00:40:28,828 --> 00:40:31,470
Thank you. We couldn't have closed
this one without you.

723
00:40:31,638 --> 00:40:32,846
That's debatable.

724
00:40:34,305 --> 00:40:35,265
You're welcome.

725
00:40:36,434 --> 00:40:38,969
Although I have to say it looks like
the spirits got it wrong.

726
00:40:39,204 --> 00:40:41,313
I guess being dead
doesn't make you infallible.

727
00:40:41,714 --> 00:40:42,903
What do you mean?

728
00:40:43,028 --> 00:40:45,317
The killer was caught,
and justice was served.

729
00:40:45,485 --> 00:40:47,968
Sure. But no blood was spilled.
Look,

730
00:40:48,279 --> 00:40:49,411
he's right there.

731
00:40:50,294 --> 00:40:51,948
- Murderer!
- Easy!

732
00:41:02,408 --> 00:41:03,509
Come on.

733
00:41:08,050 --> 00:41:09,481
That was pure luck.

734
00:41:10,244 --> 00:41:11,147
Admit it.

735
00:41:11,272 --> 00:41:13,444
- If you say so.
- I know so.

736
00:41:14,429 --> 00:41:15,731
The dead are dead.

737
00:41:16,106 --> 00:41:17,474
You can't talk to them.

738
00:41:17,642 --> 00:41:18,746
And yet I do.

739
00:41:23,923 --> 00:41:25,037
You're vergood.

740
00:41:27,266 --> 00:41:28,819
- I go this way.
- Okay.

741
00:41:29,778 --> 00:41:31,713
- It was nice seeing you again.
- You, too.

742
00:41:38,423 --> 00:41:39,746
That's with a "K," right?

743
00:41:43,527 --> 00:41:44,793
You wanna go get a coffee?

744
00:41:46,421 --> 00:41:49,191
I'll drink tea myself, but you can drink
as much coffee as you want.

745
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:50,798
Yeah, I'd like that.

746
00:41:51,549 --> 00:41:54,352
I can't right now, though.
I have to be somewhere else.

747
00:41:55,091 --> 00:41:56,536
Maybe some other time?

748
00:41:57,053 --> 00:41:58,181
Some other time.

749
00:41:58,349 --> 00:41:59,500
Sorry, not "maybe."

750
00:41:59,625 --> 00:42:01,518
Definitely.
Sometime soon.

751
00:42:03,113 --> 00:42:04,113
Call me.

